14. onclusion
arotid stenosis accounts for up to twenty percent of ischemic strokes and s. t is a potentially preventable cause of stroke, and therefore, its detection and management is of an utmost importance. any treatment modalities exist. est medical therapy including risk factor management and antithrombotic treatment should be administered effectively. n appropriately selected patients, interventions on carotid arteries should be considered in high-volume  and  centers with low periprocedural complication rates.14. Conclusion
Carotid stenosis accounts for up to twenty percent of ischemic strokes and TIAs. It is a potentially preventable cause of stroke, and therefore, its detection and management is of an utmost importance. Many treatment modalities exist. Best medical therapy including risk factor management and antithrombotic treatment should be administered effectively. In appropriately selected patients, interventions on carotid arteries should be considered in high-volume CEA and CAS centers with low periprocedural complication rates.
